Role checks apply depending on route sensitivity.

Frontend Architecture Notes

The frontend uses Next.js App Router with a proxy pattern for admin routes and public APIs.

Important frontend rules already established include:

backend base URL must come from env

admin token is stored as HttpOnly cookie

server-side auth checks route through controlled APIs

public cart state must handle missing cart UUIDs safely

local stale cart UUIDs must be cleared when cart does not exist

The cart-not-found recovery logic is especially important after database resets.

Environment Variables

At minimum, the system relies on configuration values similar to:

PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY=
APP_BASE_URL=
FRONTEND_BASE_URL=
JWT_SECRET=
SUPER_ADMIN_TOKEN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=
BACKEND_BASE_URL=

These must be configured correctly in development and production.

Security Considerations
Payment integrity

Only verified webhook calls may finalize payments and apply votes.

Admin protection

Admin APIs require JWT-based authorization and role checks.

Receipt immutability

Receipts cannot be silently changed after finalization.

Replay protection

Vote logs and request hashes help limit duplicate processing.

Auditing

Operational actions are recorded for traceability.

Environment isolation

Secrets must not be hardcoded into source code.

Production Deployment Guidance

A production deployment should include:

Reverse proxy

Use NGINX or equivalent in front of backend and frontend.

HTTPS

TLS is required, especially for admin routes and payment callbacks.

Environment management

All secrets must come from environment configuration, not source files.

Database backups

Oracle backups should be scheduled and tested.

Logging and monitoring

Application logs, webhook failures, and payment anomalies should be monitored.

Access control

Admin routes should be restricted and audited.

No localhost assumptions

All backend/frontend base URLs must come from environment variables.

Operational Runbook Notes
If cart creation fails

Check:

cart UUID handling in frontend

cart sequence alignment

backend lookup by cart UUID

stale local storage values

If nominee creation fails with duplicate key

Check:

candidates_seq

SEQ_CANDIDATE_ID

max candidate id vs sequence next value

If receipt creation fails on status

Check:

CHK_RECEIPTS_STATUS

backend inserting INITIATED

schema allowing INITIATED, SUCCESS, PARTIALLY_APPLIED, FAILED

If election creation fails due to missing sequence

Check whether backend is calling:

elections_seq

or SEQ_ELECTION_ID

and ensure both families exist if the codebase still references both.

